\int 3 x^2 \sqrt{x}\, dx + \int2 x\sqrt{x}\,dx 
  + \int 3\sqrt{x}\, dx= \\ 
\quad = \dfrac{6}{7} x^{\frac{7}{2}} 
  + \dfrac{4}{5}x^{\frac{5}{2}} + 2 x^{\frac{3}{2}}+ C \\
\text{Here, C is the constant of integration}

\int 3 x^2 \sqrt{x}\, dx + \int 2 x\sqrt{x}\,dx 
  + \int 3\sqrt{x}\, dx= \\ 
\quad = 3x^{\frac{7}{2}} 
  + 2x^{\frac{5}{2}} + 3 x^{\frac{3}{2}}+ C \\
\text{Here, C is the constant of integration}
